# The constitution governs this repository

`CONSTITUTION.md` (repo root) is the project's governing law. Read it before
any change that touches architecture, document models, geometry, the command
system, exports, or the agent surface. Where it conflicts with any other
rule, doc, or code, the constitution wins.

**The pushback mandate (Article XI):** if a request conflicts with an
article, do NOT silently comply. Name the article, explain the damage, and
propose a conforming alternative or a draft amendment. Only the user
ratifies amendments, by explicit edit to `CONSTITUTION.md`.

The articles, in one line each:

1. **Minimal core** — core = canvas paradigm (camera, tabs, journal, chrome,
   command registry); all else is a capability; no document model, geometry,
   or capability logic may depend on egui or any renderer.
2. **Performance is a feature** — 60fps canvas; no per-frame allocation or
   tessellation in paint paths (tessellate once, cache); heavy work async
   and generation-tagged.
3. **The 10% rule** — capabilities implement the deliberately chosen
   fraction of a domain actually used. "Photoshop has it" is not a reason.
4. **Honest models** — exports are serializations; graphs are extracted,
   never hallucinated; the board's styling ceiling is **SVG-expressible**
   (supersedes CSS-only), held identically by the egui painter and the
   artifact writer.
5. **One universe, portals** — the board is the only universe; generated
   views (Grid/Venn/Lens/…) are portal nodes: journaled frames,
   deterministically regenerated contents.
6. **Journal-only mutation** — every mutation is a named, invertible,
   journaled command carrying its author (human | named agent). Never mutate
   documents outside a journaled path.
7. **Command parity** — humans and agents drive the same command surface;
   agents extend the workspace with data (declarative assets), never code;
   script execution requires a future ratified amendment.
8. **Bandwidth** — the canvas is the prompt (selection/viewport/ink are
   agent context); every input modality compiles to commands; the human is
   never blocked synchronously on an agent.
9. **Slate is a linker, never a database** — links resolve through the
   `Source` abstraction.
10. **No chrome divergence** — see `.cursor/rules/shared-chrome.mdc`.
11. **Agent conduct** — pushback mandate; amendments only by user-ratified
    edits to `CONSTITUTION.md`.

Companions: `ROADMAP.md` (phase sequencing), `docs/facet-taxonomy.md`
(tools bind to facets, not formats).
